CHANGELOG

v0.1.0

Established 5-role Ansible structure targeting Debian, RedHat, and Archlinux.
Replaced all threshold-based formulas with continuous universal functions of RAM and vCPU.
Formulas are determined by continuous mathematical functions.
Cross-role data coupling enforced via system_discovery prefix convention.
systemd-boot GRUB PSI injection implemented with word-boundary regex.
MGLRU read-before-write idempotency check implemented.

v0.2.0

Split monolithic CI into 5 independent job-based workflows.
Workflows cover linting, syntax validation, formula validation, structure verification, and container tests.

v0.3.0

Added Python formula validator verifying monotonicity, bounds, and reference points across 4 formulas and 128 CPU points.
Added bash structure verifier with 10 convention checks for role files, variable prefixes, hardcoded values, Makefile rules, and ignore_errors prohibition.
All existing validation results pass across yamllint, ansible-lint production, playbook syntax, formula validator, and structure verifier.

v0.4.0

Removed all comments from YAML workflows, playbooks, and role files.
Removed all comments from Python and shell scripts.
Removed all non-log print statements from Python validator.
Removed debug print task from system_discovery.
Removed all dashes, equals, and visual decorations from documentation output.
All 5 validation checks pass with zero violations.

v0.5.0

Split each roles tasks main yml into job-based sub-files imported via import_tasks.
Each sub-file focuses on a single concern.
No task files exceed single-responsibility scope.
All 5 validation checks pass with zero violations.

v0.6.0

Extend setup-apt and setup-pip Makefile targets to include remove autoremove autoclean for stale system packages and pip packages no longer listed in requirements files.
